</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD0DB4AFFD8C954EF9EF941FE50CF72" blockId="5.[174,1232,1765,1840]" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">
Рис. 3. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6FA0C9FFD8C954EFC5F941FE6FCEB9" authority="Kovalchuk, 2014" authorityName="Kovalchuk" authorityYear="2014" box="[245,431,1765,1787]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Scardinius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ponticus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFD8C954EFC5F941FE6FCEB9" box="[245,431,1765,1787]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">Scardinius ponticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A228BA23FFD8C954EE84F941FE29CEB9" box="[436,489,1765,1787]" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: 
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFD8C954EEC2F941FE3DCEB8" box="[498,509,1765,1786]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">1</emphasis>
— изолированный глоточный зуб, голотип (NMNH–P 41/2358, лектостратотип понта); 
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFD8C954EE5BF8A4FEB6CF57" box="[363,374,1792,1813]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">2</emphasis>
— паратип (NMNH–P 41/2359). 
<taxonomicName id="4C6FA0C9FFD8C954EDF7F8A4FC1BCF57" authorityName="Cherevichne" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[711,987,1792,1813]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Scardinius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="erythrophthalmus">
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFD8C954EDF7F8A4FC1BCF57" box="[711,987,1792,1813]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">Scardinius erythrophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, современный (использован для сравнения).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD0DB4AFFDBC957EFEBFEFFFBEACAF7" blockId="6.[166,1225,187,886]" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">
A new species, as compared with other 
<taxonomicName id="4C6FA0C9FFDBC957ED84FEFFFCEEC937" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" box="[692,814,347,373]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Scardinius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="417" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFDBC957ED84FEFFFCEEC937" box="[692,814,347,373]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">Scardinius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxa, is characterized by the enormous pharyngeal tooth size, eight cogs at the grinding edge, and also the presence of beltshaped contraction at the tooth neck. They are comparable in size to the pharyngeal teeth of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6FA0C9FFDBC957EF96FE1FFE4FC997" box="[166,399,443,469]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Scardinius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="417" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tshuensis">
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFDBC957EF96FE1FFE4FC997" box="[166,399,443,469]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">Scardinius tshuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but have with a longer crown and a smaller number of cogs. Described pharyngeal teeth differ from those in the extant 
<taxonomicName id="4C6FA0C9FFDBC957EDD2FE7FFBF3C9B7" authorityName="Cherevichne" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[738,1075,475,501]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Scardinius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="417" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="erythrophthalmus">
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFDBC957EDD2FE7FFBF3C9B7" box="[738,1075,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">Scardinius erythrophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of eight cogs at the external grinding edge and well-developed hatching at the posterior occlusal plate. Pharyngeal teeth of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6FA0C9FFDBC957EDACFDBFFCBECA77" authority="Kovalchuk, 2014" authorityName="Kovalchuk" authorityYear="2014" box="[668,894,539,565]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Scardinius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="417" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ponticus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFDBC957EDACFDBFFCBECA77" box="[668,894,539,565]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">Scardinius ponticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A228BA23FFDBC957ECB5FDB8FC21CA74" box="[901,993,540,566]" pageId="6" pageNumber="417" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are similar to those in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6FA0C9FFDBC957EFF4FD9FFDF4CA17" authorityName="Cherevichne" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[196,564,571,597]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Scardinius" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="417" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="erythrophthalmus">
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFDBC957EFF4FD9FFEFECA17" box="[196,318,571,597]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">Scardinius</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFDBC957EE55FD9FFDF4CA17" box="[357,564,571,597]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">erythrophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Late Miocene strata of southern 
<collectingCountry id="F3789BDAFFDBC957EB2CFD9FFBBCCA17" box="[1052,1148,571,597]" name="Ukraine" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
by the presence of weakly developed hook, but differ from them by the more sloped grinding surface. Representatives of the new species as compared to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6FA0C9FFDBC957EC1AFDDFFC35CAD7" baseAuthorityName="Munster" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[810,1013,635,661]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Scardinius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="417" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="haueri">
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFDBC957EC1AFDDFFC35CAD7" box="[810,1013,635,661]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">Scardinius haueri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, are characterized by a wider pharyngeal tooth pedicle, and also less developed keel at the belly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD0DB4AFFDBC957EFEBFD18FCA5CAB4" blockId="6.[166,1225,187,886]" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">E t y m o l o g y. The specific name is a Latin derivation and reflects the stratigraphic position (geological age of the corresponding alluvial layer).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD0DB4AFFDBC957EFEBFD58FD8FCB37" blockId="6.[166,1225,187,886]" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. Currently, information about the geographical distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6FA0C9FFDBC957EBBDFD58FE99CB77" authority="Kovalchuk, 2014" authorityName="Kovalchuk" authorityYear="2014" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Scardinius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="417" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ponticus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFDBC957EBBDFD58FE99CB77" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">Scardinius ponticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A228BA23FFDBC957EE54FCB8FE65CB74" box="[356,421,796,822]" pageId="6" pageNumber="417" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is limited by the 
<typeStatus id="54D465E8FFDBC957ED4FFCB8FD71CB74" box="[639,689,796,822]" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">type</typeStatus>
locality. 
<location id="8EB08D91FFDBC957EC11FCBFFC5DCB77" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C66A5CFFD8C957EF9EFE8BFC1DCC48:8EB08D91FFDBC957EC11FCBFFC5DCB77" box="[801,925,795,821]" country="Moldova" municipality="Late Miocene" name="According" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">According</location>
to the high similarity of taxonomic lists, it can be assumed the opportunity to find the remnants of this species in the 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BB44130FFDBC957EFE2FCF8FEB1CB37" box="[210,369,859,886]" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">Late Miocene</collectingMunicipality>
strata of 
<collectingCountry id="F3789BDAFFDBC957EEEEFCFFFD8BCB37" box="[478,587,859,885]" name="Moldova" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">Moldova</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD0DB4AFFDBC957EFEBFC2DFC1DCC48" blockId="6.[166,1225,905,1034]" pageId="6" pageNumber="417">
